  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients over 18 years of age, without legal protection (guardianship or curatorship),

          -  Stable hemodynamic status.

          -  Affiliation to a social security scheme

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Hemodynamically unstable patients: Systolic PA &lt;10 cmHg, rapid peripheral pulse and
             spinning, mottling, obnubilation, oliguria, sweating, coma

          -  History of significant valvulopathy other than an aortic stenosis,

          -  Pregnancy.

          -  Patient under tutelage or curatelle or deprived of public right.
      </textblock>
